If you want a simple "Light" easy to sell trading bot you go with Node.js because it's highly concurrent and frontend and backend with a microservice architechture is EASY to configure and bundle together. But if you want to manipulate data. and have rich libraries or do backtesting you use Python. Especially for timeseries analysis and datetime alignment which is CRUCIAL for financial trading. Same goes for deep reinforcement learning (where you'd leverage hadoop or spark) to flag and mode nodejs libs are nothing compared to python equivalents.
